Real object effect diagram

Traditional packaging boxes are mostly made of tin, paper, plastic, etc. Although these types of packaging boxes can also protect products well, they cannot showcase the appearance and features of the product in the first place. They also cannot meet the requirements of creating differentiated packaging and enhancing product marketing effects. Transparent packaging boxes allow consumers to see the product at the first time, understand the product, and enhance consumer purchasing power.
